President Uhuru Kenyatta has pitched for the Buy Kenya, Build Kenya to create jobs for the youth drive.He visited a grand sale to export quality cheap branded new clothes.The sale at the Kenyatta International Convention Centre in Nairobi opened on Wednesday and ended on Saturday. &ldquo;This initiative accords Kenyans an opportunity to access quality, locally made affordable clothes with prices ranging from Sh100 to Sh 600 for clothes that are sold at Sh 6,000 in the US and UK,&rdquo; the President said.Uhuru ordered the Ministry of Industry, Trade and Cooperatives to extend the sale to other cities and towns. &ldquo;This initiative is important in creating jobs for youth,&rdquo; the President said. To continue to promote local production, Uhuru said the government issued VAT and duty exemption for export processing companies to sell 20 per cent of their production to the domestic market.The President said apart from creating jobs, the initiative is geared towards ensuring Kenyans have access to brand new clothes instead of second-hand garments.